{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it the law that a child has to be in a car seat when travelling in a taxi",
        "additional_details": "The current laws and regulations in place are as follows:\r\n\r\nchildren under three can travel without a child\u2019s car seat or seat belt, but only on a rear seat. \r\n\r\nchildren aged three or older can travel in a rear seat without a child\u2019s car seat if they wear an adult seat belt. \r\n\r\nThe driver can be fined up to \u00a3500 if a child under 14 isn't in the correct car seat or wearing a seat belt while you're driving.",
        "background": "Did you know that if you are travelling in a taxi with a child, a car seat is not required!\r\n\r\nA taxi is still a vehicle, just because they put a \u2018taxi roof sign\u2019 on - it doesn\u2019t mean they are protected from collisions and fatalities! The current law has no consideration for child safety.",
